"n.激怒；炽热；炎症 【英】 激怒,炽热;炎症(cond ition in which a part of the body is red, swollen and sore , esp because of infection) 【考】 反义词：mollificati on(缓和) 【记】 in(进入)+flam(火焰) +m+ation→进入火焰 →炽热 n. 点火; 发炎(表现为疼痛、红肿, 有时丧失功能); 激怒 【反】mollification(n 缓和) 【记】inflame 燃烧 + tion inflammation (n.)  ""redness or swelling in a body part,"" early 15c., from Middle French inflammation and directly from Latin inflammationem (nominative inflammatio) ""a setting on fire,"" noun of action from past participle stem of inflammare (see inflame). Literal sense in English from 1560s."
